whatever important artist needs.

92
00:07:48,581 --> 00:07:50,135
- What's that?
- Pluck.

93
00:07:53,054 --> 00:07:54,454
- Thanks.
- Sure.

94
00:08:04,731 --> 00:08:05,859
Excuse me.

95
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:13,057
Excuse me, I just need to...
If I squeezed by you here...

96
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:15,212
It's a open...

97
00:08:28,232 --> 00:08:30,050
Oh my God, are you okay?

98
00:08:30,476 --> 00:08:31,941
What the hell, uh?

99
00:08:32,951 --> 00:08:35,141
Look what you did to my bike,
you freaking idiot.

100
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:39,245
I mean, honestly, you're not even
wearing a helmet or something...

101
00:08:39,370 --> 00:08:40,769
Come on, are you serious?

102
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:44,022
You know what, junior? I think I might
need to explain something to you.

103
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,233
- I'm listening.
- It took me a lot of months

104
00:08:46,865 --> 00:08:48,915
to save up for that bike, okay?

105
00:08:50,428 --> 00:08:52,128
So it means a lot to me.

106
00:08:52,413 --> 00:08:55,617
Because not everybody gets a car
bought from their dad.

107
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:58,996
So you're gonna pay me damages.

108
00:08:59,164 --> 00:09:00,974
- That's right.
- For my bike.

109
00:09:02,058 --> 00:09:03,792
- What's your name?
- Landry Clarke.

110
00:09:05,149 --> 00:09:07,376
- What's your name?
- Jess Merriweather.

111
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:08,910
Nice to meet you.

112
00:09:09,141 --> 00:09:12,843
M-E-R-R-I-W-E-A-T-H-E-R.

113
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:15,929
That's how you spell my last name. Don't
forget that when you make up the check.

114
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,762
What the hell
is so important out here?

115
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,362
Nothing, I'm sorry...

116
00:09:58,487 --> 00:10:00,766
I think I've a wrong adress.
I just can't find this artist...

117
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,160
Who?

118
00:10:02,903 --> 00:10:04,790
Richard Sherman,
I'm gonna take off.

119
00:10:04,915 --> 00:10:07,421
- I'm sorry I bothered you.
- I'm Richard Sherman, dumbass.

120
00:10:07,703 --> 00:10:10,192
I'm Matt Saracen,
I'm your new intern.

121
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:13,070
I got a bunch of crap in here,
I need you to start moving it.

122
00:10:13,339 --> 00:10:16,950
Come on in, there's shards on the front,
I don't want any crap about it.

123
00:10:17,508 --> 00:10:20,231
- You got shoes on?
- Yes, I wear shoes.

124
00:10:20,356 --> 00:10:21,606
Close the door.

125
00:10:27,649 --> 00:10:29,049
There's the coach.

126
00:10:31,441 --> 00:10:32,965
I'm gonna go ahead and take off.

127
00:10:33,269 --> 00:10:34,919
I'll see you all later.

128
00:10:38,204 --> 00:10:39,971
Can I talk to you for a minute?

129
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:43,308
I don't know what's going on with
my football players, I need your help.

130
00:10:43,756 --> 00:10:46,056
Why did you forfeit the game, Coach?

131
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:49,033
I'm sorry?

132
00:10:49,456 --> 00:10:52,711
- I said why'd you forfeit the game?
- I heard your question.

133
00:10:54,909 --> 00:10:57,439
You have an answer to that
cause I don't understand.

134
00:10:57,564 --> 00:11:00,909
Let me tell you something. I don't have
to explain my decisions to you, Landry.

135
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:02,828
I can explain to you
that everyone gave

136
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:05,397
everything they had out there
and you just quit on us?

137
00:11:05,522 --> 00:11:07,863
Do you know what it feels like?
It's not a good feeling.

138
00:11:07,988 --> 00:11:10,438
So I'm done
and everyone else is done.

139
00:11:20,371 --> 00:11:21,710
Give me some piece!

140
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:23,390
Gimme something to work with!

141
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,430
There you go, babe!

142
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:35,945
Come here, son.

143
00:11:38,216 --> 00:11:39,615
Hey, Principal Taylor.

144
00:11:39,783 --> 00:11:42,034
- Did you see that?
- I... that was amazing.

145
00:11:42,586 --> 00:11:44,554
- That was amazing.
- Thank you.

146
00:11:44,839 --> 00:11:47,049
- I need to talk to you.
- Yes, ma'am.

147
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,733
I need you to tell me
where you live.

148
00:11:50,531 --> 00:11:51,877
2268 Oakdale Rd.

149
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:55,380
- Is that where you live?
- Yes.

150
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:56,934
2268 Oakdale Rd.

151
00:11:57,648 --> 00:12:01,053
You know that's an empty field
with a mailbox in front of it, right?

152
00:12:01,909 --> 00:12:03,909
You live on Kilroy, don't you?

153
00:12:04,307 --> 00:12:06,558
And you know that Kilroy is zoned
for East Dillon High,

154
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:07,994
isn't that right?

155
00:12:11,113 --> 00:12:14,130
I've worked so hard for the Panthers
and this team means everything to me.

156
00:12:14,255 --> 00:12:16,109
I mean,
there's no team at East Dillon.

157
00:12:16,371 --> 00:12:18,654
There is a team actually.
They're starting one.

158
00:12:18,822 --> 00:12:19,910
Well, I mean...

159
00:12:20,157 --> 00:12:22,647
Is there anything that we can do?
Can you write...

160
00:12:22,772 --> 00:12:24,724
a letter to the Governor or somehow?

161
00:12:24,989 --> 00:12:28,539
I tell you what. The only thing,
the only thing you could do

162
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:31,329
is your parents could move.
That's the only thing.

163
00:12:31,454 --> 00:12:34,204
- That's not gonna happen.
- I'm sorry, son.

164
00:12:35,518 --> 00:12:37,632
Go over there, you have
to pack up your stuff.

165
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,326
Starting tomorrow you're going
at East Dillon High.

166
00:12:40,451 --> 00:12:41,451
What?

167
00:12:41,743 --> 00:12:42,743
That's it?

168
00:12:43,049 --> 00:12:44,049
That's it.

169
00:12:45,945 --> 00:12:46,945
I mean...

170
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:52,019
I will get an A
in every single class.

171
00:12:52,144 --> 00:12:54,808
- I know, you're a good student.
- Every one. I promise you that.

172
00:12:55,755 --> 00:12:56,755
I will...

173
00:12:57,012 --> 00:12:59,695
I will do anything, I swear to you,
I will do anything...

174
00:13:00,892 --> 00:13:02,364
I'm... begging you.

175
00:13:03,116 --> 00:13:04,216
Sorry, son.

176
00:13:04,341 --> 00:13:06,827
I hate that it has
to be this way, too.

177
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,490
No, I'm okay, I'm okay...
Thank you.

178
00:13:10,615 --> 00:13:13,755
- You gonna be alright?
- I'm fine. Thank you very much.

179
00:13:13,945 --> 00:13:15,077
Go on, now.

180
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:21,569
Principal Taylor! Hey!

181
00:13:23,326 --> 00:13:26,096
I'm real sorry for lying to you.
For the whole time

182
00:13:26,573 --> 00:13:29,558
and for lying to you right now
to your face. I'm real sorry, okay?

183
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:32,352
I appreciate that, Luke.
I do appreciate that.

184
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:35,065
- It'll be alright, son.
- No, I'm fine. I'm fine.

185
00:13:35,701 --> 00:13:36,701
Thank you.

186
00:13:39,027 --> 00:13:40,725
I'll be right there, coach!

187
00:13:46,056 --> 00:13:49,017
Why hasn't the part
for Mrs. Carlson's Taurus come in yet?

188
00:13:49,142 --> 00:13:50,279
I don't know.

189
00:13:50,404 --> 00:13:53,415
The part was ordered ten days ago.
Did you order from Tahiti?

190
00:13:53,668 --> 00:13:55,353
Finish this transmission, man.

191
00:13:55,478 --> 00:13:58,170
Finish it today. You were
working on it all day yesterday.

192
00:14:00,410 --> 00:14:02,924
Just throwing it out there...
It's been well over two weeks,

193
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:06,052
- you think I'll get paid or?
- I'm waiting on money to come in.

194
00:14:06,335 --> 00:14:07,137
When?

195
00:14:07,428 --> 00:14:09,843
Seriously, could you back off
for two seconds?

196
00:14:09,968 --> 00:14:12,225
Do you have any clue
what I've got on my plate right now?

197
00:14:12,755 --> 00:14:13,945
Seriously, man.

198
00:14:14,070 --> 00:14:16,562
I'm trying to run a garage,
I gotta a pregnant wife,

199
00:14:16,687 --> 00:14:20,479
and I haven't slept for two weeks
because Mindy's reading some stupid book

200
00:14:20,604 --> 00:14:23,369
about what's supposed to happen
every 2 seconds of your pregnant life

201
00:14:23,494 --> 00:14:26,582
and now every time she farts,
she's thinking her water's breaking.

202
00:14:26,707 --> 00:14:30,243
Or, or that's she's going
into contractions. So back off!

203
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:36,249
Billy, could you pass me
that violin please?

204
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:37,542
Would you shut up?!

205
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,294
- You're hogging it!
- Shut up!

206
00:14:42,095 --> 00:14:44,845
No, that wasn't
directed towards you, ma'am.

207
00:14:46,713 --> 00:14:47,719
Where are you?

208
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:50,276
We'll send a truck out
as soon as we can.

209
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,463
When you're done with it,
I need the violin.

210
00:14:54,588 --> 00:14:56,226
Get your ass up, okay?

211
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:58,933
Get your ass up, we got a tow.

212
00:15:04,893 --> 00:15:06,364
Principal Taylor.

213
00:15:06,871 --> 00:15:07,921
Hey, y'all.

214
00:15:09,092 --> 00:15:10,492
What's it gonna take?

215
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:13,006
What conversation we're having here?
What is all about?

216
00:15:13,131 --> 00:15:14,481
I think you know.

217
00:15:15,168 --> 00:15:18,625
- Are we talking about Luke?
- Yeah, we're talking about Luke.

218
00:15:19,035 --> 00:15:20,245
So what's it gonna take?

219
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:23,338
New books for the library,
new instruments for the orchestra, what?

220
00:15:24,508 --> 00:15:27,210
Are you all coming to me
in the school parking lot

221
00:15:27,335 --> 00:15:28,777
and offering me a bribe?

222
00:15:28,902 --> 00:15:31,462
You need to be reasonable
about this, Tami.

223
00:15:31,587 --> 00:15:33,348
It's gonna hurt this kid.

224
00:15:33,590 --> 00:15:36,184
We can't let that happen to him
or to our team.

225
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:38,186
- Or to the school.
- Or to you.

226
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:41,219
I mean, what's gonna happen to you
if this goes down?

227
00:15:42,170 --> 00:15:43,608
You're gonna get lynched.

228
00:15:43,948 --> 00:15:46,522
That is so sweet.
You are so sweet to think about me.

229
00:15:46,647 --> 00:15:49,069
I appreciate that so much.
I can take care of myself, thank you.

230
00:15:49,194 --> 00:15:52,305
Think of this: that first win'll have
to be forfeited because of this.

231
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:54,460
If that happens
we might not make it back from that.

232
00:15:54,585 --> 00:15:56,871
That means we might not make it
to state this year.

233
00:15:57,039 --> 00:16:00,542
- Now do you want that?
- That boy was enrolled here illegally.

234
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:03,920
Ironically, he just happens
to be going to a school

235
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:06,172
where your husband
is the football coach.

236
00:16:08,709 --> 00:16:11,148
Would you do me a favor?
Would you go home

237
00:16:11,358 --> 00:16:13,023
and ask your husband one thing.

238
00:16:13,148 --> 00:16:15,599
Ask him who put up that mailbox.

239
00:16:16,987 --> 00:16:19,644
Because the Dillon Panthers
have been using that mailbox

240
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,354
long before I got here.

241
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:23,440
And if I want to do
a little digging around...

